15.	QUALITY AND PROTECTION OF ENVIRONMENT
The regulations of Quality Assurance Appendix to the Agreement shall apply to Supplier’s performance of Services.

16.	TERM OF MSA
This MSA shall come into force on the Effective Date of the Agreement.
This MSA shall remain valid for a term of ten (10) years from the end of the warranty period of Product last delivered under the Agreement, irrespective of the term of the Agreement, unless otherwise agreed by the Parties in writing. Thereafter, the MSA shall automatically be extended by consecutive twelve (12) month periods, unless terminated by either Party by giving six (6) months prior written notice to the other Party before such automatic renewal.
In case a Customer requires a longer contract term for this MSA, Supplier shall make diligent effort to give an equivalent back-to-back commitment to Zebracorp. The term of this MSA shall then be adapted accordingly.
Any termination or expiration of the Agreement shall be without prejudice to the rights and remedies of either Party under this MSA, surviving provisions of the Agreement or law and shall not have an effect on the validity of this MSA.

17.	ELECTRONIC DATA EXCHANGE
Upon Zebracorp’s request, Supplier shall implement, use, secure and maintain a process allowing transmission of electronical data (such as a catalogue sharing, catalogue based ordering, delivery information, scheduling, purchase order, order acknowledgement, invoice and other relevant transactions) between the Parties (directly or through intermediary provider) in the format and/or via tool specified by Zebracorp. Supplier shall ensure that all afore mentioned transmissions are: i.) authorized, and ii.) protected from improper or unauthorized access, loss, use, alteration, and destruction.

18.	MISCELLANEOUS
The Annexes to this MSA contain written workflow descriptions which may be supplemented by diagrams/illustrations to describe such workflows. In case of discrepancies between the written description and the corresponding diagrams/illustrations, the written description shall prevail.

This Software Services (Software Maintenance, Security Alert, Update & Upgrade) Annex is attached to and forms a part of the Maintenance and Support Agreement Appendix of the Software License Agreement (the “MSA”). Unless otherwise noted or evident from the context, the capitalized terms used herein shall have the meaning ascribed to them in the MSA.
